 What i suggest is that you load up one of your rain spells. From the start of the fight, go very offensive and hurt him. As soon as you see him starting to cast healing spells (torpor most likely), rain him at once. This forces him to either continue casting and eat it, or move out of the rain. Keep on pounding him and hopefully you will do damage faster than he can keep himself healed.<br><br>If he has decent resists, your rains wont do much damage and you will go oom using lures. A wizards only good chance of killing such a shaman is to get the jump on him unprepared. <p>--------------------<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16197> Asta Khaan</a><BR><a href=http://www.defiantvz.com> Defiant</a> Shaman, VZ</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/02 8:16:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=619.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sham Vs. Wiz help :(</span><hr size=1> theres a reason shaman are one of the top pvp classes.<br><br>hell at 34 I was landing poison based nukes on 55's. and a fully buffed shaman is a pretty powerful foe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 9:22:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=619.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.cenara.com/users/ce00519/sigs/zarloth_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sham Vs. Wiz help :(</span><hr size=1> <br>Prepared shamans are quite tricky to fight for wizards. <br><br>Have a load of counteract disease/poison potions. <br><br>Dispell torpor from shaman.<br><br>Don't bother too much with shock of lightning. That's a defensive spell for a wizard. Try to throw in as much damage as possible instead, using rains and high damage DDs. <br><br>In my limited wizard (level 54) experience of fighting shamans, I usually only won by PKing them ganking style, e g finding some poor troll shaman on oasis dock, opening up with a rain and then follow with an ice comet. <br><br><br> <p><BR><font face="Helvetica, Arial">Baron<a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61907"> Zarloth V`Sharatouum</a><BR>Warlock of <a target="new" href="http://www.draconictribe.com"> Draconic Tribe</a><BR>Vallon Zek</font><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 1:44:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=619.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sham Vs. Wiz help :(</span><hr size=1> Ye might want to try your question over at Shaman's Crucible:<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/">forums.interealms.com/shaman/</a><!--EZCODE AU